      "content": "Taking a single mega-dose of 50,000 IU of Vitamin D daily for several weeks is not the standard, safe approach for boosting immunity. While Vitamin D is crucial, such high acute doses can be risky and lead to toxicity. Instead, it is strongly recommended to get your current blood levels tested and then take a therapeutic dose that your doctor determines is appropriate for your specific needs.",
      "source": "target",
