      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nonsense about the risk being zero; even short, high doses of Vitamin D can cause hypercalcemia, which is a serious issue. While wellness blogs might suggest this, the medical consensus is that sustained, high-dose supplementation without monitoring is dangerous. For a quick fix, you should stick to a moderate, well-researched daily dose instead of risking a sudden, large overload. Your health is too important to gamble on anecdotal advice.",
      "source": "target",
